				<p><p>Not enough info to go on to recommend a specific set of motors, but some info to steer you in the right direction. Without a schematic or set of plans to go on I can only suggest some ideas. So here it goes.</p>

<p>Figure out the required torque for bending and twisting the wire, as well as holding it in place while it twists. I would recommend servo motors, they are fast, strong, and can be dialed in pretty precisely using a microcontroller and a feedback loop. </p>

<p>Next consider the amount of weight the motors will be moving, include tooling and materials. Select your motors based on these calculations and add in 25% extra at a minimum just a margin of error in your calculations.</p>

<p>Is your system going to use DC or AC?</p>

<p>Look online for industrial servo motors. That should get you started. You have a lot of planning to do before you pick motors.</p>
